<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/027'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=472 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/027.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/027'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Overview: Starting a Document</b>
</p><p>
With Lisa, you handle documents much the way you do in an office, but folders and
documents are stored on disks instead of in file drawers. Diskettes are like small
file drawers. Hard disks are like large file drawers.
</p><p>
DISKS hold FOLDERS with DOCUMENTS:
</p><p>
In this topic you&rsquo;ll learn to:
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100% class=list><tr><td width=16><img width=16 height=9 src='intr/liststart.png'></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Open a diskette and a folder.
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Create a new document.
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Name your new document.
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><img width=16 height=8 src='intr/listend.png'></td></tr></table></p><p>
You&rsquo;ll learn to use the File/Print menu, now in the menu bar. We&rsquo;ll add items to
the menu as they&rsquo;re introduced.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/028'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=469 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/028.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/028'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The picture at the desktop&rsquo;s lower left is an ICON that represents a diskette
named Samples. You can open the icon and see the folders and documents the diskette
contains.
</p><p>
Lisa&rsquo;s basic principle is SELECT what to work with, then OPERATE on the selection.
Opening the Samples diskette icon illustrates the principle:
<ol>
<li>SELECT (highlight) the icon by clicking in the little picture of the diskette
named Samples.
<li>OPERATE by choosing Open from the File/Print menu, now beside Topics in the menu
bar: Press and hold on File/Print. Move the pointer&rsquo;s tip over Open. Release when
Open highlights. (If Open is dim, redo step 1.)
</ol>
</p><p>
(When you see a rectangle named Samples at the desktop&rsquo;s lower right you&rsquo;ve opened
the icon: Press Continue.)
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/029'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=464 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/029.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/029'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/030'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=469 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/030.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/030'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/031'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=470 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/031.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/031'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
A WINDOW to Samples is now at the lower right of your Lisa&rsquo;s desktop. In the window
you can see the icons for two folders and a document that are on the Samples
diskette.
</p><p>
Do this to open the Supplies folder, so you can see the stationery needed to create
a document.
</p><p>
<ol>
<li>Tell the Lisa what to work with: Select (highlight) the Supplies folder icon
by clicking in it.
<li>Choose Open from the File/Print menu. Note: If Open is dim, redo step 1. (Forgotten
how to choose from a menu? Press and hold over the menu name; move the pointer
over Open; release when Open highlights.)
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/032'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=474 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/032.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/032'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/033'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=469 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/033.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/033'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/034'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=466 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/034.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/034'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
The Supplies window contains STATIONERY PAD icons named Memos and Empty Folders. Copies
of a memo form are on the Memos pad.
</p><p>
Do this to tear off a memo form from the Memos pad:
<ol>
<li>Select (highlight) the Memos pad to tell your Lisa you want to work with a memo form.
<li>Choose Tear Off Stationery from the File/Print menu. (Remember: Highlight an item before
you release.) You&rsquo;ll know you&rsquo;ve succeeded when the new document icon, Untitled, appears
next to the Memos pad.
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/035'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=467 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/035.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/035'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/036'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=470 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/036.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/036'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/037'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=476 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/037.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/037'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
It&rsquo;s a good idea to rename a new document. Otherwise you may wind up having many documents
all named &ldquo;Untitled&rdquo;: A confusing situation.
</p><p>
Follow these steps to rename Untitled:
<ol>
<li>Select (highlight) the Untitled icon.
<li>Type this: My memo<br>
(Typing mistake? Press the Backspace key at the main keyboard&rsquo;s upper right.)
</ol>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/038'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=475 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/038.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/038'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/039'><img class=screenshot alt='LisaGuide image' title='LisaGuide image' width=640 height=476 src='pics/tutorials/lisaguide/039.jpg'></a></td></tr><tr><td class=imagecaption><a href='http://guidebookgallery.org/tutorials/lisaguide/pics/039'><img border=0 align=right width=12 height=12 alt='This image can be zoomed' title='This image can be zoomed' style='margin-top: 3px; margin-left: 5px' src='intr/zoom.gif'></a></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
That&rsquo;s right! But you named the new document &ldquo;&nbsp;MyMemo&nbsp;&rdquo; instead of &ldquo;My Memo.&rdquo; We&rsquo;ll change
the name to My Memo and go on.
</p></td></tr>
</table></p>

